<tr class="DarkGreyCell">
<td colspan="2"><span class="InDarkGreyCell">
Strict diagonal dominance and a Gersgorin type theorem in Euclidean Jordan algebras 
</span></td></tr>

<tr class="GreyCell">
<td><span class="InGreyCell">- Melania Moldovan </span></td>
<td align="right"> </td></tr>

<tr class="GreyCell">
<td><span class="InGreyCell"> Abstract: For complex square matrices, the Levy-Desplanques theorem
asserts that a strictly diagonally dominant matrix is invertible. The
well-known
Gersgorin theorem on the location of eigenvalues is equivalent to this. In
